# Network Scanner

A simple Python-based network scanner that discovers devices in your local network using ARP (Address Resolution Protocol).

## Features
- Scans a specified IP range and returns a list of active devices with their IP and MAC addresses.
- Supports specifying suspicious IPs to flag during the scan.

## Requirements
This project uses the Scapy library for network packet manipulation.

## Installation

1. **Clone the repository** (or download the project):
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/your-username/network-scanner.git
